<TITLE> Flood lighting banned in elite clubs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 2 (bdnews24.com) A High Court bench has imposed a ban on three of Dhaka's elite clubs from using floodlights A High Court bench of Justice AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury and Md Delwar Hossain ordered the Dhaka, Officer's and Uttara club not to use flood lights for three months. The ruling was ordered on Sunday after the NGO, the Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh, filed a public interest writ petition. The court ordered the directors of Dhaka Electricity Supply Company and Dhaka Power Distribution Company to submit a report within seven days on the status of the court ruling. The directors were also ordered to submit a monthly report. The court also asked the government and concerned officials to explain why failure in stopping waste of power should not be declared illegal. The energy secretary, DESCO, DPDC and the presidents of the clubs are ordered to respond to this within three weeks. Deputy attorney general Nazrul Islam Talukdar represented the government in the court. bdnew
